minilzo 2.10
Downloaded from http://www.oberhumer.com/opensource/lzo/download/minilzo-2.10.tar.gz
SHA256: eb4ce543aad19533c83550746e0e9d7bcf716b35a42429e3ba17d60fa0f3e47a
License: GPL-2.0-or-later (same as tinc itself)

Four files copied verbatim from the tarball:
  minilzo.c minilzo.h lzoconf.h lzodefs.h

Provides ONLY lzo1x_1_compress + lzo1x_decompress_safe.
NOT lzo1x_999_compress (the high-compression variant) —
minilzo doesn't include it. tinc level 11 (LZO_HI) is
therefore STILL stubbed for compress; level 10 (LZO_LO)
works. Decompress works for both (same wire format,
same _safe function).

The full lzo2 library (which has _999) is 5x the size and
needs more build-system fiddling. Level 11 is rarely used
(decompress speed is identical; only compress ratio
differs); deferring it is fine.
